         <abstract>
            <p>A new class of quadrature rule methods for solving nonsingular Volterra integral equations of the first kind are introduced; these methods are based on an appropriate modification of the higher-order Newton-Gregory methods which are known to be divergent. Methods up to order six are constructed and explicitly and illustrated with numerical examples.</p>
